                <Gloss>naked</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is rare that one can employ in translating γυμνός b a term which literally means ‘naked,’ but it is possible to retain something of the metaphorical value by using a phrase such as ‘with nothing to cover’ or ‘with nothing which can be used to hide.’</Comments>
